<TITLE> Family feud kills Bharasa son </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)Khairul Islam Bharasa, younger son of former Jatiya Party MP Karimuddin Bharasa, was gunned down in his office on Monday by his own brother, said witnesses and family members. Kabirul Islam Bharasa shot his younger brother at the latter's Bijoy Nagar office over a business feud, father Karimuddin told bdnews24.com. Khairul was rushed to Square Hospital in critical condition where the duty doctor declared him dead, said the father. Kabir was the first child of his second wife and Khairul was the third, said Karim. 'Altercation' Employees at Khairul's office said the two brothers had an altercation at around 2.30pm and at one stage Kabirul shot his brother in the chest. "Kabir, entering Khairul's room, sat down in a chair, took a paper out from his pocket and placed it in front of his brother," said one employee, Anwar Hossain, quoting a fellow employee who was in the room at the time. "Khairul requested the employee to leave, saying, 'We brothers will talk now'," said Hossain. Shortly after that shots were heard from the room. Then Kabir came out carrying a gun," said Hossain. Employees rushed to Khairul's office and found he had been shot in the chest, said Hossain. Khairul was first taken to Islami Bank Hospital and later shifted to Square Hospital. No one at the office could say what happened to the elder brother. Police trying to trace Kabir Paltan police officer-in-charge Mujibur Rahman told bdnews24.com that they were trying to trace Kabir. Rahman said the suspect's car and driver were in police custody. "We are questioning the driver Taherul Islam." The two brothers lived in the same building in Banani, he added. "The quarrel was over business and property," said the OC. Khairul's wife's elder brother Imran Hossain claimed Kabir was "a drug addict and demanded money every month from the family". Other family members alleged "more people" were involved in Khairul's killing. bdnews24.c
